# Build & Deployment Best Practices

## Build Process

### Running Builds
- Use `pnpm build` from project root for full build
- Monitor for React hooks warnings and fix them immediately
- Ensure all TypeScript errors are resolved before deployment

### Common Build Issues & Fixes

#### React Hooks Warnings
- Capture ref values in variables within useEffect cleanup
- Avoid accessing `.current` directly in cleanup functions
- Pattern for fixing ref cleanup warnings:
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  const currentRef = myRef.current;
  return () => {
    if (currentRef) {
      currentRef.cleanup();
    }
  };
}, []);
```

#### Test Failures During Build
- Ensure all test mocks include required constants like `SESSION_MAX_AGE`
- Mock Next.js navigation hooks properly: `useParams`, `useRouter`, `useSearchParams`
- Remove unused imports and constants from test files
- Use literal values instead of imported constants when the constant isn't actually needed

### Test Execution
- Run `pnpm test` to execute all tests
- Use `pnpm test -- --run filename.test.tsx` for specific test files
- Fix test failures before merging code
- Ensure 100% test coverage for new components

### Performance Monitoring
- Monitor build times and optimize if necessary
- Watch for memory usage during builds
- Use proper caching strategies for faster rebuilds

### Deployment Checklist
1. All tests passing
2. Build completes without warnings
3. TypeScript compilation successful
4. No linter errors
5. Database migrations applied (if any)
6. Environment variables configured

### EKS Deployment Considerations
- Ensure latest code is deployed to all pods
- Monitor AWS RDS Performance Insights for database issues
- Verify environment-specific configurations
- Check pod health and resource usage

## Local Build & Deploy to Azure VM (surveys.aslalabs.org)

When the server doesn't have enough RAM to build, build locally and transfer the image.

### Prerequisites
- Docker Desktop running locally
- SSH key: `~/.ssh/id_ed25519_workgh`
- Server: `20.185.219.8:2222` (user: `gregcohen`)
- Build secrets in `.secrets/` directory (database_url, encryption_key, redis_url, sentry_auth_token)

### Step 1: Build AMD64 Image Locally
```bash
cd /Users/gcohen/dev/formbricks

# IMPORTANT: Use --platform linux/amd64 since server is AMD64
docker buildx build \
  --platform linux/amd64 \
  --secret id=database_url,src=.secrets/database_url \
  --secret id=encryption_key,src=.secrets/encryption_key \
  --secret id=redis_url,src=.secrets/redis_url \
  --secret id=sentry_auth_token,src=.secrets/sentry_auth_token \
  -t formbricks-local:YOUR-TAG-amd64 \
  -f apps/web/Dockerfile \
  --load \
  .
```

### Step 2: Save & Transfer Image
```bash
# Save image to tar.gz
docker save formbricks-local:YOUR-TAG-amd64 | gzip > /tmp/formbricks-YOUR-TAG.tar.gz

# Copy to server
scp -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_workgh -P 2222 \
  /tmp/formbricks-YOUR-TAG.tar.gz \
  gregcohen@20.185.219.8:/tmp/
```

### Step 3: Load Image on Server
```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_workgh -p 2222 gregcohen@20.185.219.8 \
  "gunzip -c /tmp/formbricks-YOUR-TAG.tar.gz | docker load"
```

### Step 4: Update docker-compose & Restart
```bash
# Update /Users/gcohen/dev/azure_vm/formbricks/docker-compose.yml
# Change: image: formbricks-local:YOUR-TAG-amd64

# Copy to server
scp -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_workgh -P 2222 \
  /Users/gcohen/dev/azure_vm/formbricks/docker-compose.yml \
  gregcohen@20.185.219.8:/opt/formbricks/

# Restart container
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_workgh -p 2222 gregcohen@20.185.219.8 \
  "cd /opt/formbricks && docker compose up -d formbricks"
```

### Step 5: Verify Deployment
```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_workgh -p 2222 gregcohen@20.185.219.8 \
  "docker ps | grep formbricks && docker logs formbricks --tail 20"
```

### Common Issues
- **"exec format error"**: Built ARM64 image on Mac but server is AMD64. Must use `--platform linux/amd64`
- **Build fails with OOM**: Increase Docker Desktop memory allocation (8GB+ recommended)
